cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.CL

This paper deals with feature attribution methods for tree ensemble models, which are commonly used in machine learning for tasks such as image classification and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the performance of the methods on clustering tasks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
